To run PSST locally - $ ./psst.sh run_local.txt

In the directory there is a Makefile for the tarball, which contains all files of PSST. 

To generate new tarball execute - $ make -f Makefile

This is the xml for the frontend configuration:

      <file absfname="<path>/psst.tgz" after_entry="True" after_group="False" const="True" executable="False" untar="True" wrapper="False">
         <untar_options absdir_outattr="psst" cond_attr="TRUE"/>
      </file>
      <file absfname="<path>/psst/psst.sh" after_entry="True" after_group="False" const="True" executable="True" untar="False" wrapper="False">
         <untar_options cond_attr="TRUE"/>
      </file>
      
More information about PSST - https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMSPublic/PilotStartupSiteTest
